The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Aug. 9: The RBI has asked banks to put in place a suitable mechanism to provide the benefit of the 1 per cent interest subsidy granted by the government on home loans to buy residential units of up to Rs 20 lakh. Banks are advised to put in place a suitable mechanism to ensure that the eligible borrowers avail the benefit of interest subvention for one housing unit only, the RBI said.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 9: Pharma major Lupin Ltd has filed a legal suit against rival Ranbaxy in the US, alleging patent violation of its cholesterol-lowering drug Antara. Lupin has claimed that its Swiss subsidiary, Lupin Atlantis, is the owner of the new drugs application for Antara capsules, which have 43 mg and 130 mg of micronised fenofibrate as the active ingredient.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug. 9: The State Bank of India plans to hit the market with a rights issue of about Rs 2 crore ($4.34 billion) in the fiscal quarter ending March 2011, two sources said. We have been talking to the government (regarding the rights issue), a source said.                             
	 Calcutta, Aug. 9: Srei Infrastructure Finance Company has reported a 111 per cent growth in business on a consolidated basis at Rs 3,243.38 crore in the first quarter of this fiscal. The company had disbursed Rs 1,532.70 crore in the same period last year.                             
	 Mumbai, Aug. 9: Anil Ambani-led Reliance Capital has reported a 49.04 per cent decline in net profit at Rs 76.97 crore for the first quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 151.04 crore in the same period last fiscal.
                                                                                                                          
